# 3. Core Intuition

Suppose:

```text
Current Sum = -10
```

Next element:

```text
50
```

Then:

```text
-10 + 50 = 40
```

Instead:

```text
Start fresh from 50
```

Result:

```text
50
```

Better.

---

Key Observation:

```text
Negative running sum never helps future subarrays.
```

Therefore:

```text
Discard negative sum.
```

This is the entire foundation of Kadane.

---

# 4. Main Logic

At every index:

```text
Either:

Continue existing subarray

OR

Start new subarray
```

Formula:

```java
currentSum = Math.max(arr[i],
                      currentSum + arr[i]);
```

---

# 5. Standard Kadane Algorithm

```java
public static int kadane(int[] arr){

    int maxSum = arr[0];
    int currentSum = arr[0];

    for(int i=1;i<arr.length;i++){

        currentSum =
                Math.max(arr[i],
                         currentSum + arr[i]);

        maxSum =
                Math.max(maxSum,
                         currentSum);
    }

    return maxSum;
}
```

---

# Time Complexity

```text
O(n)
```

---

# Space Complexity

```text
O(1)
```

